{"metadata": {"synopsis": "After being released from jail, Percy Talbott (Alison Elliott) travels to a town in Maine looking for a new beginning. When she arrives, she finds work at a restaurant owned by the crabby Hannah (Ellen Burstyn). She also befriends a waitress named Shelby (Marcia Gay Harden) and begins a romance with an attractive local named Joe (Kieran Mulroney). But when Hannah falls ill and Percy plans to help her sell the restaurant, Shelby's husband (Will Patton) becomes suspicious of her intentions.", "rating": "36", "genre": "Drama", "runtime": "1h 56m", "director": "Lee David Zlotoff", "studio": "", "theater_date": "", "dvd_date": "Feb 1, 2011", "box_office": "$12.6M"}, "reviews": {"reviews": ["It's really quite good and Ellen Burstyn is great", "", "Like High Plains Drifter as a Hallmark Hall of Fame presentation.", "", "", "", "", "", "", "", "Methodical and lyrical in its well-paced movement. A durable and devoted drama that is so unassuming in its execution", "", "", "", "", "Soul-satisfying movie about the spiritual process of turning pain into joy and bringing new life out of darkness.", "", "", "It's an unabashedly manipulative, melodramatic tearjerker with plot twists that Horatio Alger would have been embarrassed to use, and the fact that it's so well acted only confuses the issue.", ""], "rating": ["", "C+", "2/5", "3/5", "1/5", "B-", "3/5", "2/5", "2/5", "2/5", "4/5", "2/5", "3/5", "3/4", "2.5/4", "", "2/4", "3/4", "2/4", "4/10"], "fresh": ["fresh", "rotten", "rotten", "fresh", "rotten", "fresh", "fresh", "rotten", "rotten", "rotten", "fresh", "rotten", "fresh", "fresh", "rotten", "fresh", "rotten", "fresh", "rotten", "rotten"], "critic": ["Rachel Wagner", "Owen Gleiberman", "Rob Gonsalves", "Emanuel Levy", "Michael Dequina", "Robin Clifford", "Lori Hoffman", "Philip Martin", "Carol Cling", "Frank Swietek", "Frank Ochieng", "Linda Cook", "Jeffrey Westhoff", "Jeanne Aufmuth", "Robert Roten", "Frederic and Mary Ann Brussat", "", "James Ken